      "content": "Since your payment is around $2,500 for a \\$250,000 loan at 6.5%, roughly 80-85% of your payment in year 5 will go to interest, leaving the rest for principal. By year 25, that ratio flips considerably; you'll see perhaps 60-70% of your payment dedicated to paying down the loan principal. These figures are estimates, but they should give you a clear idea of the compounding effect working against you early on and in your favor later.",
      "source": "target",
